1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,232
Constraints define the space in which the artifact is allowed to be useful.

2
00:00:04,182 --> 00:00:13,134
They include deadlines, audience, scope, budget, permissions, prohibited actions, required claims, and statements the agent must not make.

3
00:00:13,134 --> 00:00:16,663
Write constraints as tests, not vague preferences.

4
00:00:16,663 --> 00:00:19,067
Keep it concise” is ambiguous.

5
00:00:19,067 --> 00:00:25,990
Use one page, no more than five recommendations, and put unresolved questions in a separate section” can be checked.

6
00:00:25,990 --> 00:00:28,846
Separate hard constraints from preferences.

7
00:00:28,846 --> 00:00:36,932
Hard constraints block acceptance: legal language, data boundaries, approved channels, maximum spend, or a required format.

8
00:00:36,932 --> 00:00:41,192
Preferences guide quality but may be traded off when the evidence demands it.

9
00:00:41,192 --> 00:00:44,750
Define action boundaries as well as content boundaries.

10
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:49,105
The agent may read files and draft an email without permission to send it.

11
00:00:49,105 --> 00:00:53,067
It may prepare a publishing package without permission to make it public.

12
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:56,365
Reversibility determines how much authority is safe.

13
00:00:56,365 --> 00:00:58,471
Include stop conditions.

14
00:00:58,471 --> 00:01:07,490
Pause when a source is missing, two authoritative records conflict, a cost crosses the limit, a permission is unclear, or the task expands beyond the brief.

15
00:01:07,490 --> 00:01:12,000
A useful stop returns the blocker and the smallest decision needed to continue.

16
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,451
The common failure is leaving constraints in the user's head.

17
00:01:15,451 --> 00:01:23,625
The agent fills the gap with reasonable defaults, but reasonable for the model may be unacceptable for the real audience, policy, or consequence.

18
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:27,567
First, translate important preferences into checkable limits.

19
00:01:27,567 --> 00:01:31,471
Second, separate hard constraints from negotiable guidance.

20
00:01:31,471 --> 00:01:35,625
Third, define permissions and stop conditions before execution.
